&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT KHAN ACADEMY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Khan Academy is a fast-paced, nonprofit startup on a mission to provide a free, world-class education for anyone, anywhere. We already reach millions of students every month and are growing rapidly. We’re building a library of world-class instructional and practice resources that empower learners. Whether they’re studying matrices, mitosis, or multivariable calculus, we want to offer students the resources to realize that they can learn anything.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT KHAN ACADEMY INDIA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Khan Academy India aims to deliver a world class user experience to learners in India that is locally relevant and is enabled by a strong on-the-ground team and operations. Our learning system is mastery based, which allows students to master key concepts at a pace that’s right for them before moving on to more challenging content. From serving under 500,000 learners in 2016, we are now serving almost 4 million learners a month across our websites, apps and youtube channels. These learners include both independent learners accessing us at home and teacher directed learners in schools.&amp;nbsp; Our focus is to reach the underserved by making our content accessible in local languages. Khan Academy is already available in Hindi, Hinglish, Kannada, Gujarati, Tamil, Marathi and Punjabi.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE INDIA &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCHOOL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; TEAM&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with our focus on reaching the underserved, we partner with government school systems to improve student learning outcomes by enabling teachers and students to optimally utilize the tools and resources on the Khan Academy platform. From our government partnerships, we reached 1.2 million learners last year, partnering with 8,500+ schools across various states. Our goal is to expand our scale to reach over five million learners in three years.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Schools Team works in a lean and collaborative way with our government partners, developing strong implementation plans and providing support at every step of the way. We learn and constantly iterate by gathering feedback and through data-backed insights and efficacy studies. With a small team, we have managed to reach 21,000+ teachers and 1.2 million learners across various states.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our government programs, we support teachers and teacher mentors through training sessions, resources, webinars, and by enabling peer-to-peer sharing. The Schools Team is looking to bring an on-board Training Coordinator to design and deliver professional development initiatives for teachers, teacher mentors, and administrators as part of the team’s work with different government partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a twelve-month contract-based role.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver synchronous and asynchronous modes of capacity-building initiatives for the partner programs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a team of master trainers with fluency&amp;nbsp; in Kannada language and co-facilitate high-quality training sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and document the best practices &amp;amp; challenges&amp;nbsp; emerging from the field and proactively prepare learning material to scale/address them&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data-informed decisions to continuously improve the efficiency and effectiveness of the training sessions conducted by the Khan Academy India team&lt;/li&gt;
